Swift's success in the 2010s, particularly in terms of record sales, cemented her power as a leading figure in the music industry.[169][170] Although Swift's image has transitioned from country to pop, her narrative songwriting, nurtured by her country background, offers a sense of authenticity that retains significant devotion from young audiences.[163][171] Buoyed by her strong fan base, Swift is the only artist to have four albums sell over a million copies within one week since Nielsen SoundScan started tracking sales for the Billboard 200 in 1991.[169] For New York magazine, Swift's million-selling albums, amidst an influx of streaming and a continuous decline in traditional album sales, prove that she is "the one bending the music industry to her will".[170] According to Rolling Stone, Swift's opposition to low-royalty streaming services and efforts to claim rights to her masters were two of the defining moments for the music industry in the 2010s decade.[172] Her actions have fostered debate over reforms to on-demand music streaming and prompted awareness of intellectual property rights among younger musicians.[173][174][175]

Governor of the State of Minnesota, Mark Dayton, declared August 31, 2018, as the "Taylor Swift Day" in the state, honoring Swift's two consecutive dates of Reputation Stadium Tour (August 31 and September 1) at the U.S. Bank Stadium in Minneapolis. He stated that, "through her personal and honest music, Taylor Swift has energized and inspired not only Minnesotans, but people all over the world, and is a positive influence on her fans through her example of truthfulness, grace, extensive philanthropy, and strength of character".[176][177] In 2019, Swift was named Woman of the Decade of the 2010s by Billboard[178] and became the first woman to earn the title Artist of the Decade (2010s) at the American Music Awards.[179] Financial Times named Swift one of the most influential women of 2020.[180] Billboard cited Swift's two surprise albums, Folklore and Evermore, as notable examples of how the COVID-19 pandemic forced artists to adjust their creative processes in a way that resulted in massive success.[181] Musician Jack Antonoff cited Swift as the main reason why he started producing music.[182] Swift and her work have influenced various recording artists, including Ruth B., Shamir Bailey,[183] Kelsea Ballerini,[184] Bailey Bryan,[185] Camila Cabello,[186] Sabrina Carpenter,[187] The Chainsmokers,[188] Greyson Chance,[189] Selena Gomez,[190] Ellie Goulding,[191] Conan Gray,[192] Griff,[193] Halsey,[194] Niall Horan,[195] Shawn Mendes,[196] Soccer Mommy,[197] Maren Morris,[198] Nina Nesbitt,[199] Niki,[200] Finneas O'Connell,[201] Maisie Peters,[193] girl in red,[202] Olivia Rodrigo,[203] Tegan and Sara,[204] Troye Sivan,[205] Hayley Williams,[206] and the Vamps.[207]

Personal life[]

In addition to her relationship with Joe Jonas, which ended in October 2008,[43][44][208] Swift's dating history has included other celebrities: Taylor Lautner, for three months in 2009;[209] and Jake Gyllenhaal, from late 2010 to early 2011.[210][211][212][213] Swift has also been romantically linked to John Mayer.[214] There has been speculation that the songs "Dear John" and "The Story Of Us" from her album Speak Now are about Mayer.[215] In October 2011, she revealed to Ellen that, "I don't even have, like, kind of a boyfriend. I don't have someone that I'm texting that is a guy that someday might be my boyfriend. There's like nothing going on right now."[216] Taylor dated Connor Kennedy from July-October 2012, breaking up due to long-distance issues. She dated also singer Harry Styles from December 2012-January 2013. Their relationship ended when he cheated on her, and Swift was seen leaving the island at which they were staying by herself, looking sad. Meanwhile, Styles stayed back to party with a blonde reality star.

Swift later dated DJ and producer Calvin Harris from March 2015 to June 2016 and actor Tom Hiddleston from June 2016 to September 2016. She was rumored to have started dating her boyfriend, Joe Alwyn in September 2016, and since the start they agreed to keep their relationship out of the public eye. Taylor's relationship with Joe was her longest, having lasted over 6 years. News officially broke that her and Alwyn split in March 2023. Swift later saw Matty Healy of The 1975 for a few weeks before ending it in June 2023. She has been in a relationship with Kansas City Chiefs tight-end Travis Kelce since July 2023.

Trivia[]

  • She is almost 6 feet tall standing at a height of 5 feet 11 inches (1.8 meters)[217]
  • Her lucky number is 13.
  • Her favorite color is purple.
  • She won a national poetry contest in fourth grade with a three-page poem, A Monster in My Closet!
  • She was named after American singer-songwriter James Taylor.
  • As revealed in an interview with Vogue, both of her elbows are double-jointed.
  • When she was 12, she wrote a 350-page novel called A Girl Named Girl.
  • Her favorite food is chicken tenders.
  • She has 118 Guinness World records
  • Her favorite dessert is cheesecake.
  • Her grandmother was an opera singer.
  • She has 3 cats. Meredith Grey, Olivia Benson, and Benjamin Button.
  • Her favorite song is Nelly's 2002 hit titled "Hot in Herre".
  • She has been crowned a princess of pop by none other than the renowned Queen of Pop herself, Madonna.[218]
  • Out of the 26 albums that have debuted with 1 Million sales first week, Taylor holds 7 of them[219]
  • She is the best selling artist of the 21st century with a total of 242.9M records sold worldwide[220]
  • She holds the record for the most Album of the year wins at the Grammys with a total of 4 won[221]
  • She is the first female artist to surpass 100 Billion streams across all credits on Spotify and the 2nd in general behind Drake.[222]
  • She is the first female artist to have 3 albums surpass 10 Billion streams on Spotify (Lover, Midnights, Folklore)[223]
  • She is the first artist to have 5 albums surpass 9 Billion streams (Lover, Midnights, Folklore, Reputation, 1989)[223]
  • She is the first female artist to have 6 albums surpass 8 Billion streams (Lover, Midnights, Folklore, Reputation, 1989, The Tortured Poets Department)[223]
  • Her album The Tortured Poets Department holds the record for the biggest streaming week with a total of 1.76 Billion streams in its first week[224]
  • She holds the record for the most solo songs by a female artist to reach 1 Billion streams on Spotify (17 songs)[225]
  • Each of her music videos since The Man (2020) have been self directed[226]
